            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>lemon zest</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!),<strong> half </strong>the<strong> chopped parsley </strong>(save the rest for garnish!) and<strong> remaining chopped garlic </strong>with the <strong>softened butter </strong> – this is your<strong> peri-peri butter</strong></p><p>Spread the <strong>peri-peri butter</strong> over the <strong>scored bread roll halves</strong> and add it to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray</p><p>Once the stew is almost ready, put the tray in the oven for 5-7 min or until warmed through and crusty – this is your<strong> peri-peri crusty bread</strong></p>",
